#: ../../etc/acknowledgements.rst:3
msgid "Acknowledgements"
msgstr "致謝"

#: ../../etc/acknowledgements.rst:5
msgid ""
"We gratefully acknowledge the contributions of the many people who helped"
" get this project off of the ground, including people who beta tested the"
" software, gave feedback on the material, improved dependencies of "
"Spinning Up code in service of this release, or otherwise supported the "
"project. Given the number of people who were involved at various points, "
"this list of names may not be exhaustive. (If you think you should have "
"been listed here, please do not hesitate to reach out.)"
msgstr ""
"我們衷心感謝所有幫助這個專案順利啟動的人們的貢獻，包括參與軟體 beta 測試、"
"提供教材回饋、為此次發布改進 Spinning Up 程式碼依賴項，或以其他方式支持"
"本專案的人們。鑑於在各個階段參與的人數眾多，此名單可能並不完整。"
"（如果你認為你應該被列在這裡，請不要猶豫，隨時與我們聯繫。）"

#: ../../etc/acknowledgements.rst:7
msgid ""
"In no particular order, thank you Alex Ray, Amanda Askell, Ben Garfinkel,"
" Christy Dennison, Coline Devin, Daniel Zeigler, Dylan Hadfield-Menell, "
"Ge Yang, Greg Khan, Jack Clark, Jonas Rothfuss, Larissa Schiavo, Leandro "
"Castelao, Lilian Weng, Maddie Hall, Matthias Plappert, Miles Brundage, "
"Peter Zokhov, and Pieter Abbeel."
msgstr ""
"排名不分先後，感謝 Alex Ray、Amanda Askell、Ben Garfinkel、Christy Dennison、"
"Coline Devin、Daniel Zeigler、Dylan Hadfield-Menell、Ge Yang、Greg Khan、"
"Jack Clark、Jonas Rothfuss、Larissa Schiavo、Leandro Castelao、Lilian Weng、"
"Maddie Hall、Matthias Plappert、Miles Brundage、Peter Zokhov 和 Pieter Abbeel。"

#: ../../etc/acknowledgements.rst:9
msgid ""
"We are also grateful to Pieter Abbeel's group at Berkeley, and the Center"
" for Human-Compatible AI, for giving feedback on presentations about "
"Spinning Up."
msgstr ""
"我們也感謝 Pieter Abbeel 在 Berkeley 的研究團隊以及 Center for "
"Human-Compatible AI 對 Spinning Up 相關演講提供的回饋。"
